  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2023-03-30",
    "date": "2023-04-18T18:29:03Z",
    "text": "Strengthening Supply Chains Through Truck Driver Incentives Act of 2023\n\nThis bill allows certain licensed commercial truck drivers a $7,500 tax credit in a taxable year. The adjusted gross income of such drivers may not exceed $90,000 ($135,000 in the case of a joint tax return and $112,500 for heads of household). Such drivers must have driven a truck in a trade or business for a specified number of hours in a taxable year.\n\nThe credit expires after December 31, 2024."
